            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Cato, called of Utica, a Stoic who died by his own hand after the battle of Thapsus, 46 B.C. His name was proverbial for virtue and courage.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001309": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001309",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001310": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001310",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Cautelous, cautious.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001311": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001311",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001312": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001312",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Cecrops, first legendary King of Athens.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001313": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001313",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001314": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001314",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Charax, perhaps the priestly historian of that name, whose date is unknown, except that it must be later than Nero.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001315": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001315",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001316": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001316",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Chirurgeon, surgeon.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001317": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001317",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001318": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001318",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Chrysippus, 280-207 B.C., a Stoic philosopher, and the founder of Stoicism as a systematic philosophy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001319": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001319",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001320": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001320",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Circus, the Circus Maximus at Rome, where games were held. There were four companies who contracted to provide horses, drivers, etc. These were called Factiones, and each had its distinguishing colour: russata (red), albata (white), veneta (blue), prasina (green). There was high rivalry between them, and riots and bloodshed not infrequently.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001321": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001321",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001322": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001322",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Cithaeron, a mountain range N. of Attica.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001323": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001323",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001324": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001324",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Comedy, ancient; a term applied to the Attic comedy of Aristophanes and his time, which criticised persons and politics, like a modern comic journal, such as Punck. See New Comedy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001325": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001325",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001326": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001326",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Compendious, short.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001327": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001327",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001328": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001328",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Conceit, opinion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001329": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001329",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001330": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001330",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Contentation, contentment.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001331": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001331",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001332": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001332",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Crates, a Cynic philosopher of the 4th century B.C.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001333": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001333",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001334": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001334",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Crœsus, King of Lydia, proverbial for wealth; he reigned 560-546 B.C.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001335": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001335",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001336": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001336",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Cynics, a school of philosophers, founded by Antisthenes. Their texts were a kind of caricature of Socraticism. Nothing was good but virtue, nothing bad but vice. The Cynics repudiated all civil and social claims, and attempted to return to what they called a state of nature. Many of them were very disgusting in their manners.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001337": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001337",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001338": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001338",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>DEMETRIUS of Phalerum, an Athenian orator, statesman, philosopher, and poet. Born 345 B.C.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001339": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001339",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001340": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001340",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Democritus of Abdera (460-361 B.C.), celebrated as the 'laughing philosopher,' whose constant thought was 'What fools these mortals be.' He invented the Atomic Theory.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001341": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001341",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001342": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001342",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dio of Syracuse, a disciple of Plato, and afterwards tyrant of Syracuse. Murdered 353 B.C.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001343": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001343",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001344": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001344",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Diogenes, the Cynic, born about 412 B.C., renowned for his rudeness and hardihood.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001345": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001345",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001346": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001346",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Diognetus, a painter.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001347": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001347",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001348": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001348",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dispense with, put up with.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001349": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001349",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001350": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001350",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dogmata, pithy sayings, or philosophical rules of life.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001351": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001351",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001352": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001352",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>EMPEDOCLES of Agrigentum, fl. 5th century B.C., a philosopher, who first laid down that there were &quot;four elements.&quot; He believed in the transmigration of souls, and the indestructibility of matter.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001353": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001353",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001354": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001354",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Epictetus, a famous Stoic philosopher. He was of Phrygia, at first a slave, then freedman, lame, poor, and contented. The work called Encheiridion was compiled by a pupil from his discourses.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001355": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001355",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001356": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001356",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Epicureans, a sect of philosophers founded by Epicurus, who &quot;combined the physics of Democritus,&quot; i.e. the atomic theory, &quot;with the ethics of Aristippus.&quot;</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001357": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001357",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001358": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001358",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They proposed to live for happiness, but the word did not bear that coarse and vulgar sense originally which it soon took.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001359": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001359",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001360": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001360",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Epicurus of Samos, 342-270 B.C.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001361": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001361",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001362": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001362",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Lived at Athens in his &quot;gardens,&quot; an urbane and kindly, if somewhat useless, life. His character was simple and temperate, and had none of the vice or indulgence which was afterwards associated with the name of Epicurean.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001363": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001363",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001364": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001364",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Eudoxus of Cnidus, a famous astronomer and physician of the 4th century B. C.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001365": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001365",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001366": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001366",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>FATAL, fated.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001367": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001367",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001368": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001368",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Fortuit, chance (adj.).</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001369": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001369",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001370": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001370",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Fronto, M. Cornelius, a rhetorician and pleader, made consul in 143 A.D. A number of his letters to M, Aur. and others are extant.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001371": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001371",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001372": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001372",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>GRANUA, a tributary of the Danube.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001373": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001373",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001374": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001374",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>HELICE, ancient capital city of Achaia, swallowed up by an earthquake, 373 B.C.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001375": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001375",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001376": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001376",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Helvidius Priscus, son-in-law of Thrasea Paetus, a noble man and a lover of liberty. He was banished by Nero, and put to death by Vespasian.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001377": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001377",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001378": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001378",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Heraclitus of Ephesus, who lived in the 6th century B.C. He wrote on philosophy and natural science.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001379": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001379",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001380": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001380",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Herculaneum, near Mount Vesuvius, buried by the eruption of 79 AD.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001381": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001381",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001382": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001382",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Hercules, p. 167, should be Apollo. See Muses.</p></div></div>"
        },
