            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001480": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001480",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Stoics, a philosophic system founded by Zeno (4th century B.C.), and systematised by Chrysippus (3rd century B.C.). Their physical theory was a pantheistic materialism, their summum bonum &quot;to live according to nature.&quot; Their wise man needs nothing, he is sufficient to himself; virtue is good, vice bad, external things indifferent.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001481": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001481",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001482": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001482",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>THEOPHRASTUS, a philosopher, pupil of Aristotle, and his successor as president of the Lyceum. He wrote a large number of works on philosophy and natural history. Died 287 B.C.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001483": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001483",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001484": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001484",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Thrasea, P. Thrasea Pactus, a senator and Stoic philosopher, a noble and courageous man. He was condemned to death by Nero.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001485": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001485",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001486": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/a9183b8f0c72400a/text/000001486",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-f7c9a8 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-05dbf3 twpub-a9183b8f0c72400a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Tiberius, 2nd Roman Emperor (14-31 AD.). He spent the latter part of his life at Capreae (Capri), off Naples, in luxury or debauchery, neglecting his imperial duties.</p></div></div>"
        },
